{"TopicId":198178,"ForumId":32,"TopicTitle":"Does KSP really have spyware in it?","CreatedByName":"DoctorDavinci","CreatedById":150019,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-03-08T23:45:57Z","PageNum":2,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"DoctorDavinci","CreatedById":150019,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-03-09T00:42:34Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223313928\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022171850\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221520555970\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022129964\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022linuxgurugamer\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n9 minutes ago, linuxgurugamer said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhen you first start KSP, you get asked a question about sending info back to Squad.\u00A0 Don\u0027t you think that\u0027s kind of up front?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNot in the 1.4 version ... that is missing now \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:wink:\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_wink.gif\u0022 title=\u0022;)\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"razark","CreatedById":32993,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-03-09T00:44:54Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223313935\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022171850\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221520556154\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022150019\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022DoctorDavinci\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 minute ago, DoctorDavinci said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNot in the 1.4 version ... that is missing now\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIs it really missing, or is it not asked because a previous version already asked and the setting was carried forward?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Mr. Peabody","CreatedById":173591,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-03-09T00:46:04Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223313937\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022171850\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221520556294\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002232993\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022razark\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 minute ago, razark said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIs it really missing, or is it not asked because a previous version already asked and the setting was carried forward?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI don\u0027t think the latter is the case.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"TheSystem","CreatedById":183312,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-03-09T00:46:16Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223313933\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022171850\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221520556064\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002269263\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022NoMrBond\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 hour ago, NoMrBond said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSome people were complaining that this .dll was (the) spyware, oh well.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOtherwise KSP already collected non-specific data (play session time/s, progress and technical info) but you could sort of\u00A0control the extent (well, pick one of two options). This data would now be available to T2.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nMost of the T2 data policy involves data from a T2 account, which is not required for KSP so wouldn\u0027t\u00A0apply in this case.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nKinda, the \u0022WHAT PERSONAL AND OTHER INFORMATION DOES THE COMPANY COLLECT?\u0022 section is taken from\u00A0\u003Ca href=\u0022http://www.take2games.com/privacy/\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttp://www.take2games.com/privacy/\u003C/a\u003E\u00A0which is specifically for their online services account, and doesn\u0027t apply for KSP because you don\u0027t sign up for a T2 account to play it.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv\u003E\n\u003Cdiv\u003E\n\u003Cdiv title=\u0022Found 3 errors in text\u0022\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nFunny how the people who are most outraged over this are the people who either do not understand it or didn\u0027t read it.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"DoctorDavinci","CreatedById":150019,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-03-09T00:46:27Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223313937\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022171850\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221520556294\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002232993\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022razark\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 hour ago, razark said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIs it really missing, or is it not asked because a previous version already asked and the setting was carried forward?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt is missing ... I install fresh from the store a new directory for each of my installs so no, the settings were not carried over\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"razark","CreatedById":32993,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-03-09T00:49:25Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223313941\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022171850\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221520556387\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022150019\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022DoctorDavinci\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 minute ago, DoctorDavinci said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt is missing ... I install fresh from the store a new directory for each of my installs so no, the settings were not carried over\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYeah, after I asked, I unpacked 1.4 and ran it.\u00A0 No message appeared.\u00A0 Thought it might have been a possibility.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"DoctorDavinci","CreatedById":150019,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-03-09T00:53:27Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223313943\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022171850\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221520556565\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002232993\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022razark\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n9 minutes ago, razark said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYeah, after I asked, I unpacked 1.4 and ran it.\u00A0 No message appeared.\u00A0 Thought it might have been a possibility.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nDoesn\u0027t hurt to ask ... well, in my case there are those trying to make it painful to have asked the question but that is to be expected\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Van Disaster","CreatedById":58876,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-03-09T01:30:54Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nClean install in clean directory, got the same firewall popup as every previous version has without any choices. There might be some in the launcher I suppose, but I never use it.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Cydonian Monk","CreatedById":69224,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-03-09T02:05:53Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSpyware? Who knows. I doubt it, but there\u2019s always the chance some Unity plugin has been compromised.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAnonymized user stats\u00A0and game progress data? Absolutely. And it _used_ to warn you about this, giving the option to disable it.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n...\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u2019ve not run a packet trap on KSP since downloading 1.4.0, so I can\u2019t speak to whether or not anything has changed between now and last week.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222018-03-09T08:02:25Z\u0022 title=\u002203/09/2018 08:02  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00226 yr\u0022\u003EMarch 9, 2018\u003C/time\u003E by Cydonian Monk\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Dman979","CreatedById":123837,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-03-09T02:20:28Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHey guys,\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027ve had to remove and edit a few posts in this thread. Let\u0027s take a second to calm down, and remember that personal attacks, flame-baiting, and sniping at one another are not allowed on this forum.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nCarry on!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Mr. Peabody","CreatedById":173591,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-03-09T02:21:53Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nGuys, can\u0027t we simply switch the internet connection off if Squad is indeed doing this?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Wallygator","CreatedById":97357,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-03-09T02:22:11Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/66485-squad/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u002266485\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/66485-squad/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@SQUAD\u003C/a\u003E\u00A0could easily answer this. \u00A0Hello?...\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nFrankly, since ANY\u00A0data collection is definitely\u00A0of importance or concern to most players, it is reasonable to expect (and demand) that\u00A0the game start dialogue must allow a player to TOTALLY DENY OR ACCEPT data transmission - regardless of a clean or dirty install.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222018-03-09T02:27:01Z\u0022 title=\u002203/09/2018 02:27  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00226 yr\u0022\u003EMarch 9, 2018\u003C/time\u003E by Wallygator\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Mr. Peabody","CreatedById":173591,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-03-09T02:30:42Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223314005\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022171850\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221520562131\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002297357\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Wallygator\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n8 minutes ago, Wallygator said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/66485-squad/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u002266485\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/66485-squad/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@SQUAD\u003C/a\u003E\u00A0could easily answer this. \u00A0Hello?...\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nFrankly, since ANY\u00A0data collection is definitely\u00A0of importance or concern to most players, it is reasonable to expect (and demand) that\u00A0the game start dialogue must allow a player to TOTALLY DENY OR ACCEPT data transmission - regardless of a clean or dirty install.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIf they are not answering that means guilty as charged.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Dman979","CreatedById":123837,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-03-09T02:36:37Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223314015\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022171850\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221520562642\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022173591\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022The Dunatian\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 minute ago, The Dunatian said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIf they are not answering that means guilty as charged.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt might also mean that it\u0027s 9:31 (four and a half hours after work ended) and they\u0027ve logged off for the night. \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Starman4308","CreatedById":122674,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-03-09T02:38:41Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223314015\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022171850\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221520562642\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022173591\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022The Dunatian\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n6 minutes ago, The Dunatian said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIf they are not answering that means guilty as charged.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhatever happened to \u0022innocent until proven guilty\u0022?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThere\u0027s also the strong probability that the Take Two legal team has told Squad not to say anything on the matter, and that if it\u0027s anything urgent, to refer it to them instead of saying anything themselves.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"razark","CreatedById":32993,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-03-09T02:38:51Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223314024\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022171850\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221520562997\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022123837\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Dman979\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n2 minutes ago, Dman979 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt might also mean that it\u0027s 9:31 (four and a half hours after work ended) and they\u0027ve logged off for the night. \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNow, that\u0027s way too convenient an excuse, don\u0027t you think?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:wink:\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_wink.gif\u0022 title=\u0022;)\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223314027\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022171850\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221520563121\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022122674\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Starman4308\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nJust now, Starman4308 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhatever happened to \u0022innocent until proven guilty\u0022?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHaven\u0027t you heard?\u00A0 \u0022Burden of proof\u0022 isn\u0027t a thing on the internet.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222018-03-09T02:40:14Z\u0022 title=\u002203/09/2018 02:40  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00226 yr\u0022\u003EMarch 9, 2018\u003C/time\u003E by razark\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Gordon Fecyk","CreatedById":157121,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-03-09T02:38:57Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWould posting an example of how to circumvent monitoring be a violation of forum rules?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIn prior versions I\u0027ve noticed KSP taking a very long time to launch when internet connectivity was spotty. It got to the point where I made changes to my network infrastructure to prevent this; I do IT for a living and know how to manipulate such things without hacking the software or the host PC it runs on.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Dman979","CreatedById":123837,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-03-09T02:40:42Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223314029\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022171850\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221520563137\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022157121\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Gordon Fecyk\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nJust now, Gordon Fecyk said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWould posting an example of how to circumvent monitoring be a violation of forum rules?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIn prior versions I\u0027ve noticed KSP taking a very long time to launch when internet connectivity was spotty. It got to the point where I made changes to my network infrastructure to prevent this; I do IT for a living and know how to manipulate such things without hacking the software or the host PC it runs on.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThat depends. It\u0027s probably a better question to ask over PM or in the Ask the Mods Questions About the Forums thread, so we can look at your question and give a detailed response without derailing a thread. \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Clockwork13","CreatedById":100102,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-03-09T02:41:19Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIf the deal with spyware/data collection/etc here turns out to be as shady as it seems from scrolling through this thread, then I guess 1.2.2 is the end of the line for me.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nEDIT: Might I add that the KSP steam ratings plummeted 20% after the update was released.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222018-03-09T02:43:07Z\u0022 title=\u002203/09/2018 02:43  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00226 yr\u0022\u003EMarch 9, 2018\u003C/time\u003E by Clockwork13\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Mr. Peabody","CreatedById":173591,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-03-09T02:50:31Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223314024\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022171850\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221520562997\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022123837\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Dman979\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n13 minutes ago, Dman979 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt might also mean that it\u0027s 9:31 (four and a half hours after work ended) and they\u0027ve logged off for the night. \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThere is Squad staff online as we speak.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"linuxgurugamer","CreatedById":129964,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-03-09T02:51:15Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223313937\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022171850\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221520556294\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002232993\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022razark\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n2 hours ago, razark said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIs it really missing, or is it not asked because a previous version already asked and the setting was carried forward?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI just checked on a clean install, it isn\u0027t there anymore.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBut, it was there in previous versions.\u00A0 Why are people so upset about it now?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nFrankly, if you are concerned, you can always block network access to it\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Dman979","CreatedById":123837,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-03-09T02:53:14Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223314045\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022171850\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221520563831\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022173591\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022The Dunatian\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nJust now, The Dunatian said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThere is Squad staff online as we speak.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYes, but the only one who would know- \u003Cem\u003Eand have the authorization to make a public reply\u003C/em\u003E- is \u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/149302-darth-badie/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022149302\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/149302-darth-badie/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@Darth Badie\u003C/a\u003E, and she is offline. \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAlso, for the record, pinging \u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/66485-squad/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u002266485\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/66485-squad/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@SQUAD\u003C/a\u003E pings the Squad account, not any or all users from Squad.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"razark","CreatedById":32993,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-03-09T03:06:43Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223314046\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022171850\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221520563875\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022129964\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022linuxgurugamer\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n11 minutes ago, linuxgurugamer said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI just checked on a clean install, it isn\u0027t there anymore.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIf you read my later comment, I did the same and noted the same results.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223314046\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022171850\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221520563875\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022129964\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022linuxgurugamer\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n12 minutes ago, linuxgurugamer said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nFrankly, if you are concerned, you can always block network access to it\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThis is true.\u00A0 I was merely trying to address concerns, not to throw accusations.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Ultimate Steve","CreatedById":161505,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-03-09T04:40:00Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027ve been told by someone who knows more about this than I do that KSP 1.4 appears to be sending data to Unity, Redshell, and Ghostery.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"netbumbler","CreatedById":146001,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-03-09T04:47:40Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nGrab an old version of Glasswire and just firewall it.\u00A0 Of course if you really like your mods to let you know when an update is available then firewalling KSP will break that functionality, but you can still just manually check CurseForge, Spacedock, etc., for the mod updates.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}